meanings.definition: To surpass in savor or taste.
meanings.sent1: The homemade soup outsavors the canned soup.
meanings.sent2: Her cooking always outsavors the restaurant meals.
meanings.sent3: The chocolate cake outsavors the plain vanilla cake.
meanings.sent4: The melody of the song outsavors the lyrics.
meanings.sent5: The fresh strawberries outsavor the store-bought ones.

meanings.definition: To be more flavorful or enjoyable than something else.
meanings.sent1: The new ice cream flavor outsavors the old one.
meanings.sent2: The excitement of the game outsavors the practice rounds.
meanings.sent3: The surprise ending outsavors the predictable plot.
meanings.sent4: Her kindness outsavors any material gifts.
meanings.sent5: The sunset outsavors the sunrise in beauty.
